        "body": "\r\nI am using sub components in by react application using static variables something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntext.jsx\r\nexport default function Text() {\r\n  return (<div />)      //dummy code\r\n}\r\n\r\nText.h1 = createComponent('h1', 'h1')\r\nText.h2 = createComponent('h2', 'h2')\r\nText.h3 = createComponent('h3', 'h3')\r\n```\r\nIn above code, createComponent function will return a react function component and I can use it in any application like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\napp.jsx\r\nimport Text from './text'\r\n\r\nexport default function App() {\r\n  return (\r\n     <Text.h1>Hello World</Text.h1>\r\n  )\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow I have to lazy load the Text component but I am not finding any way how to use those sub-components after that. \r\nCan anyone help on this?\r\n\r\nReact version: 16.9.0\r\n"
